verses.roman:
kāśī-miśra āsi' prabhura paḍilā caraṇe
mānya kari' prabhu tāṅre kaila āliṅgane

synonyms: kāśī-miśra—Kāśī Miśra; āsi'-coming; prabhura—of the Lord; paḍilā—fell down; caraṇe—at the feet; mānya kari'-with great respect; prabhu—Lord Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; tāṅre—unto him; kaila—did; āliṅgane—embracing.
translation: Afterward, Kāśī Miśra came and fell down at the lotus feet of the Lord, and the Lord respectfully embraced him.
